We are back with The Social Media Un-Distancing Project, Episode 3!

The purpose of the arts is not merely to present beauty and celebrate aesthetics; it is also to showcase the gruesome; it is not as humble as we often tend to portray it; it's purpose is also to showcase and bring to life the harshness of humanity. 
We loved this point Mythili Prakash, a Bharatanatyam dancer based in Los Angeles made while we chatted with her recently as part of The Social Media Un-Distancing Project! 
In conversation with Aalaap as part of our podcast series, Mythili shares navy a fascinating insight on dance, her lockdown routine, striking the balance between being a mother and a dancer at the same time and with equal passion and the importance of tuning in by tuning out. 
